\description{
\code{met_optimize_alpha_rc()} is the OptiSparseMET version of
\code{optimize_alpha_rc()} from the OptiDesign package. The \code{met_} prefix avoids
namespace conflicts when both packages are loaded simultaneously. All
arguments, return values, and internal logic are identical to
\code{optimize_alpha_rc()} in OptiDesign.

\code{met_optimize_alpha_rc()} wraps \code{\link[=met_alpha_rc_stream]{met_alpha_rc_stream()}} and
\code{\link[=met_evaluate_alpha_efficiency]{met_evaluate_alpha_efficiency()}} in an optimisation loop that searches for
the design with the best optimality criterion value among many candidate
randomisations. Three search strategies are available:
\itemize{
\item \strong{RS} (Random Restart): generate \code{n_restarts} independent designs and
return the best by criterion value.
\item \strong{SA} (Simulated Annealing): start from a random design and iteratively
propose entry permutation swaps, accepting improvements always and
degradations with probability \eqn{\exp(-\Delta / T)}, where \eqn{T}
cools from \code{sa_temp_start} to \code{sa_temp_end} over \code{sa_max_iter}
iterations. Repeated across \code{n_restarts} independent restarts.
\item \strong{GA} (Genetic Algorithm): maintain a population of \code{ga_pop_size} entry
permutations and evolve it using tournament selection, Order Crossover
(OX1), random swap mutation, and elitism.
}

\strong{Constraint preservation}: all candidate designs are generated by
\code{\link[=met_alpha_rc_stream]{met_alpha_rc_stream()}}, so family/cluster adjacency structure, genetic
dispersion, check placement, and alpha-lattice block balance are preserved
by construction in all three methods - no penalty terms are required.

\strong{Integrity guarantee}: every candidate design passes a structural
integrity check before being scored or stored as the best. The running best
is only updated when both the criterion score improves and a re-check
passes. A final integrity check is performed on the stored best before
returning to the user. If no valid design is found after all iterations,
an emergency fallback returns a single freshly constructed valid design.
}
\details{
\subsection{Optimisation target}{

All methods minimise an internal score (lower = better internally):\tabular{lll}{
   \code{criterion} \tab Internal score \tab Direction \cr
   \code{"A"} \tab \code{A_criterion} \tab Lower is better \cr
   \code{"D"} \tab \code{D_criterion} \tab Lower is better \cr
   \code{"both"} \tab Mean of \code{A_criterion} and \code{D_criterion} \tab Lower is better \cr
   \code{"CDmean"} \tab Negated CDmean \tab Higher CDmean is better \cr
}


For \code{"CDmean"}, the internal negation is transparent to the user:
\code{best_score} and \code{score_history} in the output are always reported as
positive CDmean values (higher = better). Requires
\code{treatment_effect = "random"}.
}

\subsection{Entry permutation encoding}{

For SA and GA, designs are encoded as permutations of
\code{seq_along(entry_treatments)}. A permutation is applied by passing
\code{entry_treatments[perm]} and \code{entry_families[perm]} to
\code{\link[=met_alpha_rc_stream]{met_alpha_rc_stream()}}, which then randomises and allocates entries
according to its internal logic. This means the permutation influences the
treatment-to-block assignment while \code{\link[=met_alpha_rc_stream]{met_alpha_rc_stream()}} handles all
within-block arrangement, check placement, and dispersion.
}

\subsection{Integrity checking strategy}{

Three structural constraints are verified for every candidate design:
\enumerate{
\item No entry appears more than once within any replicate.
\item All expected entry treatments are present in the field book.
\item All check treatments are present and correctly flagged as checks.
}

These checks are performed at four points in the pipeline:

\describe{
\item{Point 1 - after construction}{Inside \code{run_pipeline()}, immediately
after \code{\link[=met_alpha_rc_stream]{met_alpha_rc_stream()}} returns. Failures discard the candidate
before scoring.}
\item{Point 2 - before storing as best}{Inside \code{.update_best()}, as a
second independent check. Prevents a candidate that passed Point 1 from
being stored if its state was corrupted between construction and
comparison.}
\item{Point 3 - final check before return}{After the optimisation loop
ends, the stored best is re-checked one final time. If it fails, the
emergency fallback is triggered.}
\item{Point 4 - emergency fallback}{If no valid design is found, up to
10 fresh random constructions are attempted. The first valid one is
returned with a warning. If all 10 fail, the function stops with a
diagnostic message.}
}
}

\subsection{Failure handling by method}{

\strong{RS}: failed restarts (construction error or integrity failure) are
counted and reported. If the failure rate exceeds \code{max_failure_rate_rs},
the function stops with a diagnostic message. Below the threshold a warning
is issued.

\strong{SA}: invalid swap proposals (NULL candidate) are counted per restart but
are treated as neutral events - the current design is retained, the
temperature counter advances, and the Metropolis acceptance logic is
\strong{not} invoked. This prevents invalid proposals from distorting the
acceptance rate. If the invalid rate within a restart exceeds
\code{max_failure_rate_sa}, a per-restart warning is issued.

\strong{GA}: when an offspring fails integrity, up to \code{ga_invalid_retries} fresh
random permutations are tried as replacements. This prevents population
slots from being occupied by \code{Inf}-fitness placeholders that waste
tournament selection capacity. The total count of invalid offspring is
reported in a warning and stored in \verb{$optimization$n_failed}.
}

\subsection{Simulated Annealing temperature schedule}{
\itemize{
\item \code{"exponential"}: \eqn{T_k = T_0 \cdot \alpha^k} where
\eqn{\alpha = (T_\text{end} / T_0)^{1 / \text{max\_iter}}}
\item \code{"linear"}: \eqn{T_k} decreases linearly from \code{sa_temp_start} to
\code{sa_temp_end} over \code{sa_max_iter} steps
}
}

\subsection{Genetic Algorithm operators}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Selection}: tournament of size 2 over valid (finite-fitness)
individuals only
\item \strong{Crossover}: Order Crossover (OX1) - always produces a valid
permutation of \code{seq_along(entry_treatments)}
\item \strong{Mutation}: random swap of two positions in the permutation
\item \strong{Elitism}: top \code{ga_elitism} individuals copied unchanged to next
generation
}
}
}
